The following example shows how to convert a value expressed in cubic millimeter into a string.

    var volume = Volume.From(12, VolumeUnit.CubicMillimeter);
    string mm3 = volume.ToString(); // "12 mm3"

The following example shows how to convert a value expressed in cubic meter into a string without the unit symbol.

    var volume = Volume.From(123, VolumeUnit.CubicMeter);
    var m3 = volume.ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicMeter, symbols: QuantityUnitSymbols.NoSymbols); // "123"

The following example shows how to convert a value expressed in cubic millimeter into a string representing a cubic centimeter value.

    var volume = Volume.From(1000, VolumeUnit.CubicMillimeter);
    var cm3 = volume.ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicCentimeter); // "1 cm3"

The following example shows all the possible string conversion units.

    Console.WriteLine("{0} cm3 --> {1}", 1,    Volume.From(1,    VolumeUnit.CubicCentimeter).ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicMillimeter));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} mm3 --> {1}", 1000, Volume.From(1000, VolumeUnit.CubicMillimeter).ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicCentimeter));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} cm3 --> {1}", 1000, Volume.From(1000, VolumeUnit.CubicCentimeter).ToString(VolumeUnit.Liter));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} l --> {1}",   1000, Volume.From(1000, VolumeUnit.Liter).ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicMeter));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} ft3 --> {1}", 1,    Volume.From(1,    VolumeUnit.CubicFoot).ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicInch, "0"));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} in3 --> {1}", 1728, Volume.From(1728, VolumeUnit.CubicInch).ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicFoot, "0"));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} ft3 --> {1}", 27,   Volume.From(27,   VolumeUnit.CubicFoot).ToString(VolumeUnit.CubicYard, "0"));
    Console.WriteLine("{0} yd3 --> {1}", 1,    Volume.From(1,    VolumeUnit.CubicYard).ToString(VolumeUnit.Gallon, "0"));

The output will be:

    1 cm3 --> 1000 mm3
    1000 mm3 --> 1 cm3
    1000 cm3 --> 1 l
    1000 l --> 1 m3
    1 ft3 --> 1728 in3
    1728 in3 --> 1 ft3
    27 ft3 --> 1 yd3
    1 yd3 --> 202 gal

